 # Changelog
 
+## 2026-07-17 Australia/Sydney - ADP V0.1 task ADP-S4-P03-T050 (batched provincial A1 backfill; SHADOW)
+
+- Fiftieth task of the ADP V0.1 FINAL EXECUTION program (S4-P03). Batched provincial (A1) backfill using the T049 adapter family, expanding provincial coverage by cohort batches with a per-batch gate and failed-province isolation. release_mode SHADOW; ran from the dev environment, the production worker/cron/data untouched. New tool arxiv-daily-push/docs/pursuing_goal/v0_1/tools/province_backfill.py orchestrates the run: plan_batches, run_province (discover then fetch then normalize, with content-addressed idempotency), batch_gate (a batch passes when at least one province produced at least one well-formed A1 document), orchestrate (stop at the first failed batch; isolate failed provinces), and coverage_report. Deliverables under arxiv-daily-push/docs/pursuing_goal/v0_1/evidence/ADP-S4-P03-T050/: province_cohorts.json, province_backfill_docs.json, coverage_report.json, cost_report.json, health_report.json, known_gaps.md, and adversarial_review.md. The A1 label is earned via the connector identity check in run_province (not assumed) after an adversarial self-review confirmed the orchestrator sound. Acceptance verified (evidence/ADP-S4-P03-T050/test-results/backfill_tests.txt, ACCEPTANCE = PASS, exit 0): two cohort batches completed in order with no halt (batch 0 art-cms with Jiangsu and Shandong, batch 1 beijing-zhengce with Beijing), each passing its gate before the next started; a genuinely blocked province, Guangdong (gd.gov.cn, TLS/connection-blocked from this environment), was isolated into isolated_failures without stopping batch 0 or the run; 9 real A1 province documents were backfilled with content-addressed canonical ids, months, and correct document dates (not the meta Maketime render timestamp fixed in T049 -- Jiangsu 2026-07-14, Shandong 2026-07-09, Beijing 2026-07-14); the run is idempotent, a re-run adding 0 new canonical ids; and a deterministic negative control proved the batch gate genuinely blocks progression, since a fully failed batch 0 halted the run at batch 0 and batch 1 never ran. Realtime was not regressed since there was no deploy, the live build staying b189d3cc0703 (equal to T040). Cost (unknown != 0): production new_requests 0, D1 0, R2 0, model_calls 0. Ends IMPLEMENTATION_READY_FOR_INDEPENDENT_VERIFICATION.
+
 ## 2026-07-17 Australia/Sydney - ADP V0.1 task ADP-S4-P03-T049 (A1 provincial-portal adapter family; NOT_DEPLOYED)
 
 - Forty-ninth task of the ADP V0.1 FINAL EXECUTION program (S4-P03). A generic province-portal adapter FAMILY for A1 (province-level official), so provincial governments are covered by a few template families plus declarative site profiles rather than a business-logic codebase per province. release_mode NOT_DEPLOYED; tool-only, the production worker/cron/data untouched. New tool arxiv-daily-push/docs/pursuing_goal/v0_1/tools/adapter_a1_province.py has one generic A1ProvinceConnector class (zero province conditionals) driven by a declarative SiteProfile, with province-specific title logic confined to named override hooks (TITLE_HOOKS: strip_leading_labels, before_underscore), reusing the T031 OfficialConnector interface and T033 verify_identity for A1 classification. Deliverables under arxiv-daily-push/docs/pursuing_goal/v0_1/evidence/ADP-S4-P03-T049/: adapter family, three site profiles, override hooks, six real captured HTML fixtures (Jiangsu, Shandong, Beijing -- list + article each), contract_report.json, known_gaps.md, and adversarial_review.md. Acceptance verified (evidence/ADP-S4-P03-T049/test-results/family_tests.txt, ACCEPTANCE = PASS, exit 0): three real provincial portals pass through the SAME class via profiles -- Jiangsu (discover 75), Shandong (45), Beijing (999) -- across two template families (art-cms for Jiangsu and Shandong, beijing-zhengce for Beijing, which is the point of few families covering many provinces); each verifies as A1 on an official non-central .gov.cn domain; each yields a hook-cleaned title, a province-prefixed document number (苏政办函〔2026〕39号, 鲁科字〔2023〕143号, 京科发〔2026〕10号) and the correct document publish date (Jiangsu 2026-07-14, Shandong 2026-07-09, Beijing 2026-07-14); and the special-logic-confined-to-profile property holds since the connector class body contains zero province literals. The family was adversarially self-reviewed, which caught a real date bug (the first version's date regex grabbed the page-render <meta Maketime> timestamp instead of the document date); it was fixed by preferring the CMS pubdate meta and stripping Maketime, with three cross-checks added (date != Maketime, date == the art-cms URL path date, date == the pubdate meta) and re-confirmed sound. Fixtures were captured from the dev environment for 0 cloud cost so DIR-007 is unaffected. Realtime was not regressed since there was no deploy, the live build staying b189d3cc0703 (equal to T040). Cost (unknown != 0): production new_requests 0, D1 0, R2 0, model_calls 0. Ends IMPLEMENTATION_READY_FOR_INDEPENDENT_VERIFICATION.
